She stands three meters tall and has red hair and black skin. Kumbhanda has a human body but the head of a white horse and is said to often transform into a gourd.

Originally serving Rudra, the god of storms, Kumbhanda was later integrated into Buddhist scriptures, where she became a follower of Zouchouten (Virūḍhaka). She is also referred to as Enmiki due to her tendency to interrupt those trying to fall asleep and bring about calamities.

dvl.name: Ouroboros
dvl.desc:
A dragon, also known as the World Serpent, that symbolizes eternity. In ancient Greek, its name holds the meaning, "the serpent that eats its own tail." In keeping with that name, it is often depicted as eating its own tail, forming a circle without end, which is said to be representative of "death and rebirth" as well as "immortality."
Some of Ouroboros's aspects are shared with Oceanus from Greek mythology and Leviathan from the Old Testament.

dvl.name: Walpurgisnacht
dvl.desc:
Her nature is helplessness. She symbolizes the fool who continuously spins in circles. She bears a striking resemblance to the mysterious stage-constructing Witch, whose name has been handed down through the course of history.
She possesses enough power to potentially annihilate all things organic and inorganic without a trace.
This Walpurgisnacht was born from the memories of a certain magical girl who wandered into an Aura Gate, where wishes can be granted in strange ways.

dvl.name: Madoka Kaname
dvl.desc: A second-year student at Mitakihara Middle School. She is a very kind girl who cares deeply for her friends. Though she has little experience as a magical girl, she has a secret power.

dvl.name: Homura Akemi
dvl.desc:
A girl who transferred to Mitakihara Middle School, the same school that Madoka Kaname attends. Cool, collected, and beautiful, she excels at both sports and academics.
In combat, she is very adaptive, able to wield heavy weapons with polished finesse.

dvl.name: Krishna
dvl.desc:
A hero appearing in Hindu Mythology, who is the 8th incarnation of the god Vishnu. He appears whenever the world is in danger. His name has the meaning "all-attractive."
He was raised by cattle herders and grew up to become a handsome young man who was waited upon by many women. He spent his days playing his flute, dancing, and making merry. As an adult, he was a great tactician, using his knowledge and wisdom to achieve tremendous success in battle.
Ultimately, while meditating, Krishna lost his life when the hunter Jara mistakenly shot an arrow into the sole of his foot, which was his weak point.

dvl.name: Thoth
dvl.desc:
An almighty god from Egyptian Mythology. He is often depicted as a man with the head of a crested ibis or baboon.
He stands opposed to the evil god Seth and is an ally and follower of the good gods  Osiris and Isis.
Thoth is also the god of writing and keeps records of the names of the dead in Osiris's court. Additionally, he is well versed in magic and has taught Isis many spells.

dvl.name: Inanna
dvl.desc:
A goddess in Sumer Mythology presiding over love, beauty, war, and good harvests.
Her name means "Queen of Heaven." She was thought to be one and the same as the harvest goddess Ishtar, as well as Aphrodite and Venus, and was worshipped by many.
She was also known as a goddess who drove off foreign invaders and it is said her power was great enough to send even male gods running.

dvl.name: Baphomet
dvl.desc:
A goat-headed demon that governs Black Masses. His name is sometimes used as a catch-all term for demons in general. During the Inquisition of the Templar Knights, this name was mentioned as the evil that was worshiped at the time. Witches are known to worship him as well.
A freak accident at the Summoning Portal caused these demons with a different appearance to appear.

dvl.name: Pixie
dvl.desc:
Small fairies found in southwest Britain. They are cheerful and like to play pranks. Their physical appearance changes from region to region and they always act mischievously. Though they love pranking the common folk, they are known to aid farmers and are generally considered good fairies.
A freak accident at the Summoning Portal caused these demons with a different appearance to appear.

dvl.name: Vanitas
dvl.desc:
The manifestation of a part of Vanitas who is omnipresent in the worlds' Dragon Stream. As a miracle of the gods given divine form itself, Vanitas has long witnessed the corruption of the Dragon Stream by humanity's malice.
However, deification drove Vanitas into a frenzy. It stood against the Neo Liberators as a powerful enemy capable of bringing about the Extinction Event. After being defeated in a direct confrontation, it shifted its focus from observing all humanity to fixating on a single individual.
The danger of Vanitas bringing about the end of humanity looms evermore.

dvl.name: Hariti
dvl.desc:
A goddess also known by the name Kishimojin, who is believed to watch over and protect children.
Though originally a wicked demon that devoured children, she was struck with intense grief when the Buddha hid the youngest of her 500 children, who she adored most of all.
After the Buddha taught her the pain of a parent who has lost their child, Hariti became a good deity and is said to have started eating pomegranates instead of children.

dvl.name: Mitra-Buddha
dvl.desc:
The reborn form of Maitreya, who is said to bring salvation to the world. He is a bodhisattva who has become a Buddha through the cycle of reincarnation and also possesses attributes of the ancient Persian deity Mitra.
Though he guides humans to salvation, granting them serenity through moksha, he also mercilessly hands down punishment on those who would interfere with that endeavor.

dvl.name: Macha
dvl.desc:
One of the three Goddesses of Battle appearing in Celtic Mythology, whose name comes from the word for "plain."
She is said to guide fighters into a spiral of fury and madness, and then feast upon the heads of those who fall in battle. "Bait for the Fruits of Macha's Tree" refers to a custom in which the heads of enemies would be used to adorn gates as an offering to her.
In order to prevent the invasion of a foreign people, she fought against Balor of the Evil Eye, but was slain along with her husband Nuada.

dvl.name: Harpy
dvl.desc:
Wind spirits appearing in Greek mythology, also known as Harpyia. Depicted as creatures with the body of birds and the heads of women.
Though cowardly, preferring to avoid fighting, harpies also have a knack for mischief. Originally, they were goddesses of the island Crete.
In their respective mythology, they are said to have appeared as the three sisters Aello (Storm), Ocypete (Swift Foot), and Celaeno (Dark Clouds).

dvl.name: Artemis
dvl.desc:
A goddess of hunting and virginity appearing in Greek mythology, who is said to be a twin of the sun god Apollo.
She bears the title "Goddess Who Rains Down Arrows," and is also recognized as a bringer of pestilence and death.
Artemis fell in love with Orion, son of Poseidon, but Apollo, who was displeased by this, tricked Artemis into shooting Orion dead. It is said that, in order to comfort his daughter, Zeus raised Orion into the heavens and made him into a constellation.

dvl.name: Moloch
dvl.desc:
An ancient Middle Eastern god worshipped in Canaan.
He is also known as "The Ruler of the Land of Tears," and "The Horrid King Besmeared with Children's Blood and Parents' Tears." A bronze statue of a man with a bull's head was placed at his altars.
In the Bible, he is known as a savage pagan god.
A freak accident at the Summoning Portal caused these demons with a different appearance to appear.

dvl.name: Hydra
dvl.desc:
A giant snake-like monster with 9 heads.
In Greek mythology, this creature is said to possess infinite vitality. If one of its heads were to be chopped off, two new ones would immediately grow from the wound.
The Hydra had a deadly venom for which there was no antidote, and went around ravaging villages before being slain by the hero Heracles.
Afterward, it is said to have risen to the heavens and become the Hydra constellation.

dvl.name: Michael
dvl.desc:
An entity born out of Vanitas's Malice. A new threat created using the data of Michael, one of the four Heralds, who stand above all other Divine.
The real Michael is an intelligent and courageous warrior who is said to have defeated Lucifer, the angel who rebelled against God, and sealed him under the earth.
He is said to have performed many other miracles, earning the faith of many people. Even today, there are still churches and sanctuaries in Europe dedicated to him.

dvl.name: Anthrasax
dvl.desc: The dark God of Destruction that brought the world to the brink of ruin in only seven days. She is a wicked, grotesque god who seeks the annihilation of all humanity and civilization. She was sealed by the combined might of the four kingdoms, one of which was Meta-llicana. But because of an invasion by the Dark Rebel Army, it is feared she will rise again.

dvl.name: Dark Schneider
dvl.desc:
A legendary wizard who has continued reincarnating over the course of 400 years, thereby increasing his magic might.
After dying in the great war and reincarnating as a baby, he was sealed by the Great Priest Geo.
However, he revived 15 years later in the kingdom of Meta-llicana. 
Though extremely handsome and invincible, he is also haughty, inconsiderate, and a total womanizer. The only one who can reign him in is Geo's daughter Yoko.

dvl.name: Arshes Nei
dvl.desc:
A half-elf, born to a human and a Dark Elf. She is a magic swordsman known as the "Empress of Thunder."
She wields the Raijinken (lightning sword), which is inhabited by the Thunder Beast Nue, and is adept at using lightning magic.
She is one of the Four Divine Kings of the Dark Rebel Armies, but was originally the foster daughter of Dark Schneider. Even now, she harbors a strong love for him.

dvl.name: Fionn mac Cumhaill
dvl.desc:
A hero from Celtic Mythology. He is leader of the warrior group known as the Fianna Knights, who were tasked with protecting High King Cormac.
He was known as "Fionn," meaning "golden hair," because of his blond hair and fair skin, but his given name at birth was Deimne.

When training under the he druid Finn Eces, he was ordered to cook the Salmon of Knowledge. When he licked a bit of salmon fat that had gotten onto his thumb, he gained its wisdom. From then on, it’s said he could tap into that wisdom simply by licking his thumb.

dvl.name: Danu
dvl.desc:
The mother goddess of Celtic Mythology.
She is the mother of a family known as the Tuatha De Danann, and is also said to be the mother of the world itself, from which all life sprung forth.

It is said that, to this day, Danu's large body is still lying on Earth. The Munster region in Ireland, where faith in her is widespread, is said to be especially blessed by her.

dvl.name: Nuwa
dvl.desc:
A goddess appearing in Chinese Mythology.
She is depicted with a human head and a snake body, and is said to have created humanity.
She is one of the Three Sovereigns, and is said to be either the wife or sibling of Fuxi, another of the Three Sovereigns.
When the four pillars supporting the world collapsed, Nuwa is said to have repaired them. She is also said to be the creator of humanity, having made humans out of mud.

dvl.name: Medusa
dvl.desc:
A monster that appears in Greek mythology, as well as one of the three Gorgons.
Medusa has snakes for hair, skin covered with blue scales, golden wings on her back, and fangs in her mouth. It is said that those who look into her eyes will be turned to stone.
Other descriptions envision her as having a normal and beautiful female form, save for her serpentine hair.
She was beheaded by Perseus, who had the aid of the goddess Athena.

dvl.name: Peri
dvl.desc:
Fairies or spirits from Persian lore that have white, dove-like wings and are often depicted as beautiful women.
They live off of fragrant scents such as musk, and their blood is said to turn into jewels when it dries.
They are proficient in various types of magic, such as transformation, flight, and prophesying. They often assist heroes with their magic and sometimes even become their wives.

dvl.name: 使用せず
dvl.desc: 使用せず

dvl.name: 使用せず
dvl.desc: 使用せず

dvl.name: The 6th Angel
dvl.desc:
An entity strikingly similar to the Angel that attacked New Tokyo-Ⅲ. It is a fake created by Jabo Kakuryu in order to rattle Shinji Ikari's heart.
Though normally appearing as a kind of crystalline octahedron, it will change shape and attack based on the situation. The original 6th Angel fought with the Evas and was destroyed by a positron cannon.
